   <S PAR='1' RSNT='1' SNO='1'>E. The Preeminent One in Both</S>
   <S PAR='2' RSNT='1' SNO='2'>God's Old Creation and God's New Creation</S>
   <S PAR='3' RSNT='1' SNO='3'>Christ is the preeminent One in both God's old creation and God's new creation Col 1:15-18 .</S>
   <S PAR='4' RSNT='1' SNO='4'>F. The Head and All the Members of the Body</S>
   <S PAR='5' RSNT='1' SNO='5'>and the One Who Is in All the Members of the Body</S>
   <S PAR='6' RSNT='1' SNO='6'>Colossians 1:18a and 3:10-11 reveal that Christ is the Head of the Body, all the members of the Body, and the One who is in all the members of the Body.</S>
   <S PAR='7' RSNT='1' SNO='7'>G. The Life of the Believers</S>
   <S PAR='8' RSNT='1' SNO='8'>Christ is the life of the believers Col 3:4 , who is revealed into the believers Gal 1:16 , who lives in and with the believers Gal 2:20 , who is formed in the believers Gal 4:19 , who makes His home in the believers Eph 3:17 , to the glorious image of whom as the firstborn Son of God the believers as the many sons of God are transformed 2 Cor 3:18; Rom 8:29 , and whom the believers live and magnify through the bountiful supply of His Spirit Phil 1:19-21 .</S>
   <S PAR='9' RSNT='1' SNO='9'>There is no comparison between Paul's word and James's word.</S>
   <S PAR='10' RSNT='1' SNO='10'>H. The Need to Experience</S>
   <S PAR='11' RSNT='1' SNO='11'>Such a Marvelous Christ</S>
   <S PAR='12' RSNT='1' SNO='12'>Without experiencing such a Christ, how can a believer have the genuine Christian perfection, which is the issue of a life lived not by the natural life of the believer but by such a marvelous Christ who lives in him?</S>
   <S PAR='13' RSNT='1' SNO='13'>I. The Defect in James's Presentation of Christ</S>
   <S PAR='14' RSNT='1' SNO='14'>The above portrait of Christ also shows the defect in James's presentation of Christ.</S>
